abstract: David Schiff's opera "Gimpel the Fool," which had its premiere last season, returned to the stage of the 92d Street Y on Thursday night in a slightly revised form and with two major changes in cast. It was again presented as part of the series called Jewish Opera at the Y.
headline_main: Opera: Revised 'Gimpel the Fool' by David Schiff
headline_print_headline: Opera: Revised 'Gimpel the Fool' by David Schiff

abstract: MORE than in any other choreography, perhaps, we look for the personality of Isadora Duncan in her  work. There are glimpses there of the free spirit and the intense idealist and of the inspiration of nature and history.

abstract: ORLANDO, Fla., March 1--It rained on Arnold Palmer's parade today with Dan Pohl and Dave Eichelberger locked in a seven-under-par lead when the third round of the Bay Hill Classic was halted.
